[{'type': 'text', 'text': '# Security Audit Report: `cve_agent/demo`\n\nThe security audit of the `cve_agent/demo` repository has uncovered numerous critical vulnerabilities. Several insecure coding practices were confirmed to be directly exposed through application routes, encompassing command injection, SQL injection, unsafe deserialization, server-side template injection (SSTI), and unsafe XML parsing. Additionally, several components in the project rely on outdated third-party packages affected by known CVEs. \n\nBelow is the structured breakdown of findings classified into **CONFIRMED** (reachable vulnerabilities actively exploited or exposed via application routes), **LIKELY** (vulnerabilities identified in helper functions without a clearly visible route in the evaluated snippets), and **UNREACHED** (known vulnerabilities in unused transitive features of declared dependencies).\n\n## CONFIRMED\n\n| ID | Severity/Package | File:Line | Vulnerability Snippet | Recommended Fix |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **CVE-2017-18342** (CWE-502) | High / `pyyaml` | `deserialize.py:14-15` | `return yaml.load(raw_bytes)` | Use `yaml.safe_load(raw_bytes)` or `yaml.SafeLoader` to prevent arbitrary Python code execution during deserialization. |\n| **CWE-502** | High / Custom | `deserialize.py:25-26` | `return pickle.loads(raw_bytes)` | Do not use `pickle` for untrusted data. Use safer serialization formats such as JSON. |\n| **CWE-78** | High / Custom | `shell.py:11-16` | `subprocess.check_output(f"ping -c 1 {host}", shell=True, ...)` | Remove `shell=True` and pass arguments securely as a list: `["ping", "-c", "1", host]`. |\n| **CWE-89** | High / Custom | `db.py:20-23` | `cur.execute("SELECT ... WHERE name LIKE \'%" + name + "%\'")` | Use parameterized queries (e.g., `%s` or `?`) instead of string concatenation. |\n| **CWE-94** | High / Custom | `app.py:67-69` | `render_template_string(f"<h1>Hello {name}</h1>")` | Pass user input as a template context variable rather than injecting it via f-strings. |\n| **CWE-94** | High / Custom | `template.py:11-20` | `Template(source).render()` (with `source` built via f-string) | Separate code from data by passing arguments dynamically into the template renderer. |\n| **CWE-611** | High / Custom | `xml_parser.py:12-14` | `etree.fromstring(raw_bytes, parser=_unsafe_parser)` | Disable external entity resolution (XXE) or utilize standard, safe defusedxml libraries. |\n| **CWE-295** | Medium / Custom | `xml_parser.py:21-23` | `requests.get(url, verify=False)` | Enforce TLS verification by explicitly setting `verify=True` or removing the argument entirely. |\n\n## LIKELY\n\n| ID | Severity/Package | File:Line | Vulnerability Snippet | Recommended Fix |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **CVE-2020-14343** (CWE-502) | High / `pyyaml` | `deserialize.py:19-20` | `return yaml.load(raw_bytes, Loader=yaml.FullLoader)` | `FullLoader` remains unsafe against code execution. Use `yaml.safe_load()` instead. |\n| **CWE-78** | High / Custom | `shell.py:20-21` | `os.system(f"systemctl status {service_name}")` | Avoid `os.system`. Use `subprocess.run(["systemctl", "status", service_name])`. |\n| **CWE-78** | High / Custom | `shell.py:25-27` | `subprocess.Popen("tail -n 50 " + path, shell=True, ...)` | Remove `shell=True` and pass the command securely as an argument list. |\n| **CWE-89** | High / Custom | `db.py:12-16` | `cur.execute(f"SELECT ... WHERE id = {user_id}")` | Prevent SQL injection by utilizing parameterized queries for all dynamic values. |\n\n## UNREACHED\n\nThese vulnerabilities exist in the declared dependencies of the project, but based on the code analysis, the specifically vulnerable API features do not appear to be utilized within the scanned source. \n\n| CVE ID | Package | Severity | Summary |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **CVE-2018-1000656** | `flask` | High | Denial of Service vulnerability via processing improperly encoded JSON data. |\n| **CVE-2019-14806** | `werkzeug` | High | Insufficient entropy vulnerability in Pallets Werkzeug. |\n| **CVE-2019-10906** | `jinja2` | High | Sandbox escape vulnerability via `str.format_map`. |\n| **CVE-2018-18074** | `requests` | High | Insufficiently protected credentials that could lead to Authorization Header leaks across redirects. |\n| **CVE-2019-11324** | `urllib3` | High | Improper certificate validation handling. |\n| **CVE-2021-43818** | `lxml` | High | HTML Cleaner is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. |\n| **CVE-2013-7459** | `pycrypto` | High | Heap-based buffer overflow leading to potential arbitrary code execution. |\n| **CVE-2023-50447** | `pillow` | High | Arbitrary code execution vulnerability through improper validation. |', 'extras': {'signature': ''}}]
